As shown in Fig. 3
                     , both the samples SAPO-34-S and SAPO-34-S-F show an obvious uptake near saturation pressure in the isotherms compared with the sample SAPO-34-C, implying the occurrence of meso- or macropores. Moreover, the samples SAPO-34-S and SAPO-34-S-F exhibit nearly identical micropore as SAPO-34-C (Table 1
                     ), revealing that all the zeolite samples have similar crystallinity. Furthermore, the SAPO-34-S and SAPO-34-S-F samples demonstrate an enhancement in the external surface area as well as mesopore volume, further confirming that a secondary porosity was successfully introduced into the zeolite samples.
